<TITLE> West Indies to stage World Twenty20 in 2010 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MOHALI, India, Oct 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - West Indies will stage a world Twenty20 championship in April-May 2010 instead of the one-day Champions Trophy, the International Cricket Council (ICC) said on Saturday. Switching to the shorter format tournament would help avoid repeating a major one-day event in successive years because the World Cup is scheduled to take place in the sub-continent in 2011, ICC chief executive Haroon Lorgat told a news conference. The ICC executive board will choose three venues from among those to be nominated by the West Indies board in January. The decision will avoid staging the Champions Trophy and World Cup in successive years as has happened recently. This year's tournament in Pakistan was postponed to September next year due to security concern
